  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Crispen the duck skin</strong></p>\n<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7, and boil a kettle.</p>\n<p>Using a sharp knife, score the <strong>duck skin</strong> on a diagonal, being careful not to cut through to the meat. Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>.</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>scored duck</strong>, skin-side down, to a cold, dry pan over a low-medium heat. Cook for 10-15 minutes, skin-side down only, or until the skin is golden and crispy.</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1590.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1590.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1590.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1590.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1590.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Cook the sweet potatoes</strong></p>\n<p>Peel and cut the <strong>sweet potatoes </strong>into bite-sized pieces.</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped sweet potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> over a high heat and bring to the boil.<br /><br />Cook for 10-15 minutes or until fork-tender.</p>\n<p>Once done, drain and return them to the pot and cover to keep warm.</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1590.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1590.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1590.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1590.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1590.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Start the pomegranate sauce</strong></p>\n<p>Meanwhile, re-boil half a kettle.</p>\n<p>Dissolve 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong><span class=\"text-highlight\">Knorr </span>chicken stock cube</strong> in 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>.</p>\n<p>Once the duck fat has rendered, transfer the <strong>duck</strong> to a baking tray, skin-side up, and set it aside for later.</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1590.new.step.3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1590.new.step.3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1590.new.step.3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1590.new.step.3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1590.new.step.3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Finish the pomegranate sauce</strong></p>\n<p>Remove the <strong>duck fat</strong> and wipe the pan clean.<span class=\"text-highlight\"> You can keep the duck fat in the fridge to use again on roast potatoes.</span></p>\n<p>Return the pan to a medium heat. </p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chicken stock</strong>, <strong>pomegranate molasses</strong> and <strong>honey</strong> and cook for 8-10 minutes, stirring frequently, or until a thick and sticky sauce remains.</p>\n<p>Once done, remove from the heat and reheat just before serving.</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1590.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1590.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1590.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1590.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1590.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Roast the duck</strong></p>\n<p>Meanwhile, put the <strong>duck breasts</strong> in the oven for 10-12 minutes for <strong>medium</strong>. Cook for a further 3-5 minutes if you prefer your duck <strong>well done</strong>. Once cooked, set the <strong>duck</strong> aside to rest for at least 10 minutes. </p>\n<p>Add the <strong>Tenderstem</strong> <strong>broccoli</strong> to a tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable <span class=\"text-highlight\">oil</span></strong><span class=\"text-highlight\">. Add a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and put it in the oven.</span></p>\n<p>After 5 minutes, add the <strong>pistachios</strong> to one side of the tray and cook for <span class=\"text-highlight\">another 3 minutes or</span> <span class=\"text-highlight\">until toasted.</span></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1590.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1590.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1590.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
